==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Etherin
<hw>E"ther*in</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white,
crystalline hydrocarbon, regarded as a polymeric variety of ethylene,
obtained in heavy oil of wine, the residue left after making ether; --
formerly called also <altname>concrete oil of wine</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Etherization</ent>⟦br⟧
